cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to predict sentence specificity. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves unsupervised domain adaptation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The use of regularization techniques and posterior distribution also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques. Finally, the paper also mentions the potential of their work in improving dialogue generation systems, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
